 </m:semantics>
</m:math> is greater in the nozzle. The pressure <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{P rSub { size 8{2} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> in the nozzle must be atmospheric since it emerges into the atmosphere without other changes in conditions.</para></example>
